Jeff Villepique<//name>
<Date>1349473194540</Date><Rating>2<//Rating>< review>
I wouldn't believe how bad a shop could be if I hadn't seen the results myself!  I have 2 friends who each had major work done by D&G about a year apart.  The sloppy work (failure to torque bolts) caused major damage to both of their vehicles.  Both had an oil seal leak at the front of the engine (Toyota truck and Isuzu trooper).  D&G did not tighten the crankshaft bolt, causing the pulley/balancer to become loose, ovalize and chew up the CRANKSHAFT.  Both times, D&G refused responsibility and told each guy they needed a new ENGINE!  I helped one friend buy a new crankshaft key and $190 pulley, and after many hours of labor, make his Toyota work again.  He in turn helped the friend with the Isuzu.  I saw it myself.  People make mistakes (though 2 for 2??) but seriously, refusing to own-up to your own damage is the lowest.  Avoid D&G AT ALL COST!< /review>

<text>Pros:
- 9 beers on tap
- 99 bottled beer selections (according to the website)
- good for groups
- you can bring in outside food (like La Farine bread yummmm)
- SAMPLES! (so glad I was able to try the Mocha Bomb before committing to a drink)
- Ritterguts Gose was tart and just slightly sweet

Cons:
- lack of lighting
- I wasn't sure how to order food (now I know to order at the bar)
- fairly pricey for the portion size (could be worth it if you really enjoyed that beer)

Bottom line: I'm not a fan of beer and this place did not change my opinion of it. There are far more impressive taprooms in San Francisco, but this is pretty decent for Elmwood/Oakland. If you enjoy beer, I definitely recommend a visit here.</text><pics>None<//pics>< response>

< review>
The five stars and kudos goes to Kelly who cleared up a big mess with my membership. Somehow, for many years I was charged for two memberships and overcharged for my wife's membership. I didn't realize it until I took a good look at my bank statements.

This could have been swept under the rug or punted towards their corporate office. However, Kelly took the bull by the horns and cleared everything up. It took tremendous effort and know how. Kelly pulled it off spectacularly.

I received a refund of back charges. My dues are slightly less than what they should have been. Appropriate apologies and thanks for my patients. My attorney who happened to be overseeing all this while we're working on another project was impressed with the outcome and the effort Kelly put forward.

24 Hour Fitness not only averted losing a member, but also garnered full support of said member thanks to Kelly.

Thank you very much Kelly for all you had done!</review>

My wife and I had a membership here for awhile - price is a little high because it's a 24 Hour Super Sport. There were always towels available when we walked in. I never had a wait for the running machines (big problem I had with LA Fitness down the hill) and never had a "usage" time. <user>118445700443551020427< /user><user_name>SoCal Gal</user_name><Date>1465062822190</Date>< rate>

< review>
I started on May 22,2016.so far, I'm happy.when I have asked for help I received the information and help.ive been encouraged to step outside of my box.i go off peek times.I have not used the showers BC I'm not a "public facilities" user.i do not use public restrooms (unless I look like a sloum skier at the starting gate), I will however say, they appear well kept.the dispensers were full.
I only pay $39.99 per month. I hold a military dependant card but was not given a discounted rate as I don't have TriCare medical insurance. I have not seen the female manager described in another post as yet, it doesn't mean she doesn't exist, it just means I haven't seen her yet.
Even though I could be any of the Personell Granny they are all very helpful, encouraging and supportive and have, again, encouraged me to "try" a yoga,zumba,spinning, & "Silver Sneakers¬Æ" group class... I,personally,am not ready for that just yet..i will eventually but not right now.There are a lot of rows of different solitary machines I'm not familiar with so I can't name them all but there is spinning bikes, I thought it was a bike but it's a spinning machine but was gently shown the correct machine I was looking for. on June 1 the gentleman who was helping me on my treadmill encouraged me to try to Run, I did.0.3mi at 3.8 mph! Better than what I did do which was power walking.As for Kids Klub, children will "act up" when not in the presence of their authority figures.Its not "Terrible Two's" it's a lot of " stuff" plus you as an outsider can't "control" a child you've just met! That has to be earned. Also, if a child is doing something"wrong" that the adult doesn't want the child to do... diversionary tactics always work well, BC children at that age have the attention span of a gnat! Get them involved in hammering or circle games, "ring-around-the-rosie" is always a good one for that age. Keeps them occupied for minutes!
Anyway, I'm quite happy with the facility. Living in this Crap-hole desert with the temps in triple digits with 0% humidity it's Hot like Hell.so, I'm happy to be able to at least get out of the house for an hour to go "do" something other than spend money I don't have on stuff I don't need at the joke they all call a Mall or take my life in my own hands at the "Lake" in Hesperia or Spring Valley. choose your poison - ya know?</review>

< Review>
I lost my husband April 2015. i became very ill . went to my doctor she said i was very seriouly depressed and gave me  meds, but said this will only help temporarly. and recommeded going to the gym. so i joined 24 hr fitness. it was the answer to my prayers. the frist day i went to the pool aquatics. and there i  met the most caring and loving people. at first i felt like i didnt belong there but i was wrong. I have never felt so welcome in any other place with alot of people. this is the place to be to renew yourself. i have lost weight and inches with all the programs and equipment to help do this . And im 63 yrs old with arthitis. i highly recommend 24hr fitness in Apple Valley Ca.</Review>

< Review>
I had the Gardenburger here. The Gardenburger is not a particularly adventurous order. And it's not the current craze in terms of veggie burger (that would be the Impossible Burger). I still like it, though. I don't need my veggie burger to resemble meat. I quite LIKE the consistency & flavor of the Gardenburger. That said, I really enjoyed the one I got from Dijon's. It was just tasty & nice. I would definitely order it again (maybe tonight!). A pleasant surprise...<//Review>

My boyfriend and I passed by this place at around 10.45 pm tonight and have always wanted to try it out since we live nearby, so we decided to walk in and grab an order to go. As we walked in, the lady at the counter just stood there and stared at us and did not say a word. We took a moment to look at the menu for a good couple of minutes and just as we were about to order, she tells us "We are closed, we have put the sign out that our store is closed." 1) This was completely untrue as the sign out at the store was still shown as "Open", even as we left. 2) She could have told us beforehand that they were closed as we walked in and save us the time and trouble of standing there looking at the menu and deciding what we were about to order while she awkwardly stared at us.

All she had to do was just tell us that they were closed or the kitchen was closing when we walked in from the beginning and we would have understood but instead she chose to stare at us and not say anything while we were standing and deciding in front of the counter.

Nice little place. Staff is very friendly and happy hour has outstanding value. Getting drinks was a bit challenging with only one very good, but overworked, bartender. The Carne asada on my nachos had a lot of fat and gristle in spots. The carnitas on my taco was very tasty. The spicy hot sauce was pretty hot and had great flavor. I would definitely go back again.</Text>

112443961655468089006<//user_id>
<name>daniela pacheco<//name><Date>1595980173397</Date><rate>5<//rate>< review>
Love this place for years and so does my family! Some of us are vegetarian which can be challenging finding a good menu that everyone will enjoy. Se√±or Grubby's cooks knows how to make a tasty veggie burrito! This is our top three options for easy dining. Service is quick and the food is often hot even after some travel. I only have one caution recently, the same day my card was charged here, there was a another charge at a gas station near $100. Not sure if my info was compromised a week or more earlier but I hadn't used the card for a week and the charge landed the same day within a few hours after food purchase.  I declined my receipt from the guy at the register. I hope that wasn't incentive to think I don't check my card regularly. No bad press though against the restaurant. Still a loyal customer. Just noting here in case there is a trend.< /review>

< review>
On a warm Saturday night in Oceanside, California, four college aged boys walked into Sen√≥r Grubby‚Äôs. Not expecting much these boys were in no way shape or form prepared for what was about to happen to them. As their life was about to change forever. When the burritos and nachos came to their table what happened next was nothing short of a miracle. What entered their mouths was probably the greatest thing to ever happen to things in all of human history. Half way through my Carlsbad burrito i realized I was fully erect and blood flow was beginning to not get to my brain. Luckily, the servers were on top of their game and gave each of the boys the equivalent to an olympic swimming pools worth of water to ensure our survival. After finishing the meal four men collected themselves and walked outside. Thank you grubby‚Äôs, we will never forget you.< /review>

<user>114503398065429087770</user>< review>
Being a major fan of the Senior Grubby's in the village of Carlsbad, I was enthralled to learn they had just opened a new location in downtown Oceanside just blocks from my house.
Same great food and service in a new fun and relaxed environment.
Awesome location just blocks from the beach with lots of space and outdoor seating. I ordered a shrimp fajita and a Razzle-Dazzle burrito. Both amazing! I could tell the shrimp was fresh as well as all the veggies. They had the same salsa selection as the Carlsbad location and tons of drinks to choose from.
Zoey took my order and was very friendly, accommodating, and knowledgeable about the menu items.
Great local Mexican spot. Must visit!!<//review>

In November of 2018 I experienced a life changing accident that left my car completely totaled and would later find permanently impacted my body. The temporary relief of getting out of my car and finding the woman who had hit me was unharmed, was immediately followed by another wave of panic as I called my insurance to find out my policy had been cancelled that month due to an automatic payment not going through. < review>
Everything hinges on the time that you visit. Do not take this lightly. Early morning is beautiful there. Weekdays are less crowded than weekends. It will expose you to nature that you may never have known existed. On the other hand, if all you want to do is get a walk in, you can cover a half mile walking from one end of the lake to the other. Plenty of parking. Check the south end parking lot if you find other areas full. Photographers will have no problem finding a subject in the birds and nature that surround the lake. It's a big place. A playground. A work-out area. Fishing. Lakeside benches. And plenty of pathways to walk.</review>

< pics>
[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNvGANFw5ENXy592pcmfinA0Hmgzo2efIeLYOLJ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pics>
<Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
This is a marshland park, with small catch & release fishing docks tucked away, up & down the park  this is a park with lots of waterfowl, you will not get close to the water at this park. It is built this way because its a Marshland preserve! Swampy, low flow water behind the tall bull rushes, large boulders and full size marsh plants keeping the waters edge as natural as possible.
You won't dip your finger in or look for little minnows that the ducks are eating, because its not that kind of water, think of it as a river that would be hard to maneuver through the bushes and tall reeds to get to so you kinda see it from afar.
A beautiful park with nice winding trails on lots of landscaped land. Nice play areas, wide open spaces , parking in lot or on street.
Geese, large ducks, small ducks.<//Review>

< rate>

< Text>
Love Love Love this park. I love how vast it is and that there are to different areas for the kids to play. For the most part, it's a pretty flat park and fishing friendly. The kids love to watch the ducks and geese. The park is beautiful and the groundskeepers really take care of it. The bathrooms have been very clean from what I've seen. The park can get very crazy on holidays and street parking on Vermont is kind of dangerous because cars fly down the street. There are a couple different lots that do not connect which I don't like. I do like that the park abides by it's hours and the parking lot is closed at a certain time. Haven't seen any questionable characters there either.<//Text>

< Date>
1604494321896</Date>
<text>This Park is founded and dedicated to my amazing boyfriend's (Christopher Malloy) grandfather Ken Malloy. In 1937 on a foggy morning Ken was driving down the road and bumped into some cows that were quietly grazing on the side. So he pulled over to make sure everything was ok.This Is when he first set eyes on the beautiful land and fell in love. Eventually the land became Ken Malloy Harbor Regional Park. Since that day Ken was a man that dedicated his life to care for the trees, bushes ,flowers, and wild life. He started the camp for the kids. So the kids had a beautiful place to spend their days. Ken use to go down to the park everyday for hours and hours. He would also water the trees by hand. The park was his life, dreams, and passion. Until he passed away January 1, 1991 at the young age of 79. My boyfriend's grandmother ( Mary Ellen Malloy) said that Ken told to her one day that the park was his baby.... Ken Malloy was a quiet hero in this neighborhood. Even on his deathbed when he could no longer speak but only through he's eyes the Audubon Society promised him that they will continue his work that he begun at Harbor Park/White Point and they did they kept that promise. And now in 2020 Ken Malloy's spirit and memories live on in the park that made him so happy to be alive. He found his passion and he lived his dreams. Ken was a Great, Loving, Hard Working, Selfless Husband ,Father, and Grandfather on top of being a dedicated Longshoreman ,Park Ranger ,Conservationist, Hiker, Hunter, Fisherman and Grocery Store Owner. Ken is dearly missed by many including his grandson that got to enjoy a short time with him but says "he remembers running around in the house that Ken built with his own two hands and playing in the backyard that Ken also built. As a kid it seemed like grandpa's backyard was a forest it was the coolest place to run play and jump. I remember him sitting in the back watching me play. I can even remember the smell of my grandpa. He was always willing to hang out with me and he never was a crabby man he was always a happy man That I can recall." I just wanted to give everyone that visits the park a little story of a man I wish I could of met but never got a chance to a little bit of the wonderful life he lived and the great things he did for his neighborhood. So when your going to the park or at the park or leaving the park just remember why that park is there today and remember who was the man that loved the park that you to get to enjoy and pass on the story with someone else to always remember this beautiful mans name....... RIP Ken Malloy< /text><pics>None</pics>< UserId.>

Lots of open space, nice walk paths, BBQ areas and tables, fishing piers (catch and release) playground and body weight fitness gym area. <user>106716035276093118011< /user>< username>
Rosa Melgoza<//username>
<Date>1528776196288< /Date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< Review>
This is by far my favorite park. There is ample parking and walking paths are wonderful. You get views of the lake plus the marsh surrounding the lake attract a multitude of bird variations. The park is super green, park rangers patrol the area and there is even a gym with a boot-camp type obstacle course. My dogs love it here. The only issue I have with the park are the drinking fountains. I believe there is only one in the whole park near the ranger/admin building. If you want an open space, this is definitely a place to clear your mind.<//Review>

1559458459246<//Time>
<Rating>4< /Rating>< review>
The park is nice and clean and surrounds the Machado lake. There are areas for 'catch and release' for fishing. There's also a jungle gym for kids and an outdoor exercising equipment.

You might be able to see ducks and there is a small area that dips into the lake which could be there area the ducks hang out at.

There are restrooms available with a hand washing area . There's plenty of parking for free.

Overall it's a nice spot to chill if you're visiting the hospital across the street or just in the area. You can see views of the lake and the refinery off towards Wilmington< /review>
